### Alternative: Custom Controller (if not using Spring Boot Actuator)

```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/health")
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class HealthController {

    private final DataSource dataSource;
    private final RedisTemplate<String, String> redisTemplate;
    private final WebClient webClient;

    @GetMapping("/liveness")
    public ResponseEntity<Map<String, Object>> liveness() {
        return ResponseEntity.ok(Map.of(
            "status", "UP",
            "timestamp", Instant.now()
        ));
    }

    @GetMapping("/readiness")
    public ResponseEntity<Map<String, Object>> readiness() {
        Map<String, Object> details = new HashMap<>();

        boolean dbOk = checkDatabase();
        boolean redisOk = checkRedis();
        boolean apiOk = checkExternalApi();

        boolean isReady = dbOk && redisOk && apiOk;

        details.put("status", isReady ? "UP" : "DOWN");
        details.put("database", dbOk ? "UP" : "DOWN");
        details.put("redis", redisOk ? "UP" : "DOWN");
        details.put("externalApi", apiOk ? "UP" : "DOWN");

        return isReady 
            ? ResponseEntity.ok(details)
            : ResponseEntity.status(503).body(details);
    }

    private boolean checkDatabase() {
        try (Connection conn = dataSource.getConnection()) {
            return conn.isValid(2);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return false;
        }
    }

    private boolean checkRedis() {
        try {
            return "PONG".equals(redisTemplate.execute(
                (RedisCallback<String>) conn -> conn.ping()));
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return false;
        }
    }

    private boolean checkExternalApi() {
        try {
            return Boolean.TRUE.equals(
                webClient.get().uri("/health")
                    .retrieve()
                    .bodyToMono(Boolean.class)
                    .timeout(Duration.ofSeconds(2))
                    .block());
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return false;
        }
    }
}
```

---

### Summary of Best Practices Applied:

- **Liveness**: Minimal checks (just DB) — avoids killing pods due to transient Redis issues
- **Readiness**: Full dependency check — prevents traffic routing to unhealthy instances
- **Startup Probe**: Helps with slow initialization (caches warm-up, schema validation, etc.)
- **Cascading failures**: Redis and external API **do** make the service unready
- **Timeout protection** on all external calls
- **Detailed metrics** for observability (Prometheus compatible)

